British Prime Minister Boris Johnson was fined for breaking the COVID-19 rules of his government by attending social gatherings, including his own birthday party. Who'd have thought the brave PM, walking unscathed in the streets of Kyiv, would be ambushed by a birthday cake in London?! Editors: Sudeshna Sarkar, Yuan Xin Chief editor: Ge Jing Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)